Discuss: Some of your biggest screw-ups, weirdest or most unusual confrontations, games where you felt completely overwhelmed, etc.

I'll start:

I just came from a TB game where I went Ezreal ADC. The entire enemy team (aside from one gold player) was platinum. I'm just an unranked scrub and ADC is one of my worst roles. {{champion:32}}

replies.body:
{{champion:40}} 
I once was going to play Janna support, called support, selected Janna, waited a bit, 10 second left, I locked in. Then someone randomly locked in another support with just a second left on the clock. I wound up going top. I forget who I was matched against but the game did not start well, I died once really early. Then 3 people tower-dove me at about 10 minutes, I got a triple-kill somehow, and I wound up carrying the game. I generally don't worry too much about seeing unconventional picks anymore. It was a very stressful and awkward game but in the end it was very fun.
